UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407679900885
AB  - Index data become inconsistent over time when publishing agencies change the method of aggregation. However, when they do so, they often republish some previously published data using the new method. It is shown that such overlapping data can be exploited to reconstruct the data series in an ‘optimal’ manner to provide for consistent series, using results from the theory of aggregation.
